'''Kukumiohiko Shrine''' (くくみおひこじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Yōrō|Q153814|qid=Q153814|1=Yōrō, Gifu}}, {{ill|lt=Yōrō District|Q1155060|qid=Q1155060|1=Yōrō District, Gifu}}, {{ill|lt=Gifu Prefecture|Q131277|qid=Q131277|1=Gifu Prefecture}}. It is the Kukumiohiko Shrine of {{ill|lt=Tagi District|Q11431050|qid=Q11431050|1=Tagi district}} in {{ill|lt=Mino Province|Q864156|qid=Q864156|1=Mino Province}} listed in the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|qid=Q11064932|lt=Engishiki|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}, and its former rank under the {{ill|lt=modern shrine ranking system|Q712534|qid=Q712534|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines}} was {{ill|lt=gōsha|Q134917316|qid=Q134917316|1=Gō-sha}}. It is also written as Kugumiohiko Shrine.

It stands along the {{ill|lt=Tōkai Nature Trail|Q4249812|qid=Q4249812|1=Tōkai Nature Trail}}, on the mid-slope near the northern end of the {{ill|lt=Yōrō Mountains|Q8062668|qid=Q8062668|1=Yōrō Mountains}}.

=== History ===
The founding period is unknown. Because the ''{{ill|lt=Shoku Nihon Kōki|Q1041301|qid=Q1041301|1=Shoku Nihon Kōki}}'' records that it received the divine rank of Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade in {{ill|lt=Jōwa (Japan)|Q1075605|qid=Q1075605|lt=Jōwa|1=Jōwa (Heian period)}} 5 ({{ill|lt=838|Q23838|qid=Q23838|1=838}}) from {{ill|lt=Emperor Ninmyō|Q349271|qid=Q349271|1=Emperor Ninmyō}}, it is presumed to have been founded no later than the early {{ill|lt=Heian period|Q193292|qid=Q193292|1=Heian period}}.

There are records that during the {{ill|lt=Sengoku period (Japan)|Q204023|qid=Q204023|lt=Sengoku period|1=Sengoku period}} it was called Kugumihohiko Daimyōjin, and in the {{ill|lt=Edo period|Q184963|qid=Q184963|1=Edo period}} it was called Kugumiohiko Jinja Daimyōjin. When it became a gōsha in {{ill|lt=Meiji|Q3125096|qid=Q3125096|1=Meiji era}} 6 ({{ill|lt=1873|Q7757|qid=Q7757|1=1873}}), it was renamed Kukumiohiko Shrine.

=== Enshrined deity ===
*Kukumiohiko-no-Kami
:What kind of deity Kukumiohiko-no-Kami is remains unclear. The following theories exist:
#The same deity as Tatamihiko-no-Mikoto of {{ill|lt=Ibuki Shrine|Q11379321|qid=Q11379321|1=Ibuki Shrine}}. However, deities of Ibuki Shrine also have multiple theories, including {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Yamata no Orochi|1=UNKNOWN}}, {{ill|lt=Ame-no-Hoakari-no-Mikoto|Q10940411|qid=Q10940411|1=Amenohoakari}}, and {{ill|lt=Ugayafukiaezu|Q1373935|qid=Q1373935|lt=Kusayafugō-no-Mikoto|1=Ugayafukiaezu}}; Tatamihiko-no-Mikoto (also called Ebisudake-no-Kami, Kibuki-no-O-no-Kami, or Ibuki-no-Kami) is regarded as the deity of {{ill|lt=Mount Ibuki|Q2624360|qid=Q2624360|1=Mount Ibuki}}.
#Kukumihohiko-no-Kami, a divided deity of Ama-no-Tobeno-Mikoto. Details of Ama-no-Tobeno-Mikoto are unknown, but it is presumed to be {{ill|lt=Ōtonoji and Ōtonobe|Q11073597|qid=Q11073597|lt=Ōtobe-no-Mikoto|1=Otonoji and Otonobe}}.

=== Precinct shrines ===
*Sansha Shrine ({{ill|lt=Izanagi|Q813858|qid=Q813858|lt=Izanagi-no-Kami|1=Izanagi}}, {{ill|lt=Izanami|Q682306|qid=Q682306|lt=Izanami-no-Kami|1=Izanami}}, {{ill|lt=Konohanasakuyahime|Q1781862|qid=Q1781862|lt=Konohanasakuya-hime-no-Kami|1=Konohanasakuya-hime}})
*Shinmei Shrine ({{ill|lt=Amaterasu|UNKNOWN|lt=Amaterasu Ōmikami|qid=Q455602|1=Amaterasu}})

